<p>
  This option adds display modes to DXGL, even if they are not available on the current display. These modes only appear if supported by the current scaling mode.<br />
  The following items are available:
</p>
<h1>Common low resolutions</h1>
<p>
  Adds low-resolution modes that are common on older Windows based computers. This option is recommended to be enabled to improve compatibility with some older games.<br />
  The following video modes are added:<br />
  <code>
    320x200, 70Hz refresh<br />
    320x240, 60Hz refresh<br />
    320x400, 70Hz refresh<br />
    320x480, 60Hz refresh<br />
    640x400, 70Hz refresh
  </code><br />
  In addition, if the postprocess scaling is set to automatic, this will attempt to add pixel-doubled resolutions for the following:<br />
  <code>
    640x350, 70Hz refresh -> 320x175<br />
    640x400, 70Hz refresh -> 320x200<br />
    640x480, 60Hz refresh -> 320x480<br />
    640x400, 70Hz refresh -> 320x400<br />
    640x480, 60Hz refresh -> 320x480<br />
    640x400, 60Hz refresh -> 640x200<br />
    720x400, 70Hz refresh -> 360x200<br />
    720x480, 60Hz refresh -> 360x240<br />
    720x400, 70Hz refresh -> 360x400<br />
    720x480, 60Hz refresh -> 360x480<br />
    800x600, 56Hz refresh -> 400x300<br />
    800x600, 60Hz refresh -> 400x300
  </code>
</p>
<h1>Uncommon low resolutions</h1>
<p>
  Adds several low resolution modes commonly used on older DOS and VESA 2.0 based computers.<br />
  The following video modes are added:<br />
  <code>
    360x200, 70Hz refresh<br />
    360x240, 60Hz refresh<br />
    360x400, 70Hz refresh<br />
    360x480, 60Hz refresh<br />
    400x300, 60Hz refresh
  </code>
</p>
<h1>Uncommon SD resolutions</h1>
<p>
  Adds a few uncommon and widescreen standard-definition resolutions, including modes used on old VESA 2.0 displays, EGA displays, and small widescreen displays.<br />
  The following video modes are added:<br />
  <code>
    512x384, 60Hz refresh<br />
    640x350, 70Hz refresh<br />
    640x360, 60Hz refresh<br />
    720x400, 70Hz refresh<br />
    720x480, 70Hz refresh<br />
    960x540, 60Hz refresh<br />
    960x600, 60Hz refresh<br />
    960x720, 60Hz refresh<br />
    1024x600, 60Hz refresh
  </code>
</p>
